'''Oathkeeper''' is one of two [[Valyrian steel]] longswords made from [[Ice]], the greatsword of [[House Stark]], under orders of Lord [[Tywin Lannister]]. While initially given to [[Jaime Lannister]] by Lord Tywin with the intention of making it an heirloom of their house, Jaime instead gave it to [[Brienne of Tarth]]Â for the task of rescuing [[Sansa Stark]].Â Its sister blade is [[Widow's Wail]].

sections.History:
===[[Season 4]]===
[[File:6de15b65107d9de914ca800c1ec637ba.png|thumb|Oathkeeper's hilt as seen in &quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;.]]
Tywin gives the sword to his son Jaime, intending for him to be released from his vows as Lord Commander of the [[Kingsguard]] and rule over [[Casterly Rock]] in his stead. When Jaime refuses, Tywin lets him keep the sword anyway and tells him that a one-handed man needs all the help possible.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Two Swords]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Following King [[Joffrey Baratheon|Joffrey]]'s death, Jaime tasks [[Brienne of Tarth|Brienne]] with finding [[Sansa Stark]] and get her somewhere safe before Cersei locates her. As a parting gift he gives her the sword, as he knows it was reforged from Ice, so she can protect [[Eddard Stark|Ned Stark]]'s daughter with Ned Stark's own blade. She considers a name for a few moments, before choosing &quot;Oathkeeper&quot;.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

When Brienne and Podrick encounter [[Arya Stark]] and [[Sandor Clegane]], Oathkeeper's Lannister qualities cause Arya and Sandor to be suspicious of Brienne. When the situation turns hostile, Brienne uses Oathkeeper in combat for the first time against Sandor. However, she wins the duel by knocking Sandor off a cliff after brutal hand-to-hand combat.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
